## Common Color Usage Examples

### Text Colors
- Primary text: `univer-text-gray-800` (#181C2A)
- Secondary text: `univer-text-gray-400` (#979DAC)
- Disabled text: `univer-text-gray-300` (#CDD0D8)

### Background Colors
- Primary background: `univer-bg-gray-100` (#EEEFF1)
- Secondary background: `univer-bg-gray-50` (#F9FAFB)
- Active/Selected: `univer-bg-primary-50` (#F3F5FF)

### Border Colors
- Default border: `univer-border-gray-200` (#E3E5EA)
- Active border: `univer-border-primary-500` (#466AF7)

Remember to always prefix class names with `univer-` when using these colors. 